tabber (0.1.6) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add: dual-pane SFTP file browser. Opens from a new Files button on
    each SSH tab, the hamburger menu's File Transfer... item, or
    Ctrl+Shift+T. Replaces the old single-file transfer dialog.
  * Local filesystem on the left, remote filesystem on the right. Each
    pane has a path bar, Up/Home/Refresh buttons, column headers
    (Name / Size / Modified), and a hidden-file toggle.
  * Click semantics: single click selects, double click navigates into
    a folder, triple click uploads or downloads the selected file or
    folder (recursive for folders via psftp put -r / get -r).
  * Right-click context menus: Upload/Refresh on the local pane;
    Download, Rename, Delete, New Folder, Refresh on the remote pane.
  * Bottom status bar with a pulsing progress bar during transfers and
    deletes, and explicit success / failure summary on completion.
  * Recursive folder delete on the remote side (psftp's rmdir only
    removes empty dirs, so the backend walks the tree).
  * Password auth for sessions without an SSH key: in-memory password
    prompt on open; passed to psftp via -pw for the window lifetime
    only, never persisted.
  * New PsftpBackend wraps a persistent psftp -batch subprocess with a
    nonce-framed request/response protocol so command output can be
    reliably demultiplexed. LC_ALL=C forced so ls -l dates are stable.

 -- George Cottrell <georgecottrell@email.com>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 11:30:00 -0500

tabber (0.1.5) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add: detach a tab to a new window. Three ways to trigger:
    right-click tab > Move to New Window, drag a tab onto the desktop,
    or Ctrl+Shift+D on the active tab.
  * Add: tabbed connection dialog with full PuTTY/plink coverage.
    - Quick Connect: name, protocol, host, port, user, SSH key.
    - SSH: compression, X11 forwarding, no-PTY, no-shell, Pageant
      agent, agent forwarding, certificate file.
    - Tunnels: editable list of Local / Remote / Dynamic (SOCKS)
      port forwards.
    - Proxy: jump host (-J), proxy command, IPv4/IPv6 only,
      logical host name (-loghost).
    - Terminal: group, tab color, notes (existing organization fields).
  * Sessions persist all advanced options in Tabber's JSON metadata;
    basic fields remain compatible with PuTTY's session format.

 -- George Cottrell <georgecottrell@email.com>  Thu, 16 Apr 2026 21:00:00 -0500

tabber (0.1.4) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix: closing tabs is now instant. The close-page handler called a
    nonexistent Adw.TabView API, raising AttributeError on every close
    and triggering GTK's default close path on top of our own.
  * Fix: cancel auto-reconnect timer on tab close so a destroyed
    terminal can't try to reconnect 3 seconds later.

 -- George Cottrell <georgecottrell@email.com>  Thu, 16 Apr 2026 12:00:00 -0500

tabber (0.1.3) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix: clicking sessions inside group folders now connects correctly.
  * Add connect button (play icon) on each session row.
  * Add right-click context menu on sessions: Connect, Edit, Delete.
  * Add right-click context menu on group folders: Connect All, Add Connection.
  * Connect All opens tabs for every session in the group at once.
  * Add Connection pre-fills the group name in the new connection dialog.

